  • Classes in com.gridgraph.storage used by com.gridgraph.bulkload.heap 
    Class and Description
    IGraphStorage
    The IGraphStorage interface should be implemented by any class whose instances are intended to provides graph database storage for single graph, thus most of IGraphStorage interface method doesn't specify graph, instead this storage will be attached to a concrete graph instance and all its operations will be applied on that graph.

    Interface to represents GridGraph messages storage which is used for a graph computing The IMessageStorage interface should be implemented by any class whose instances are intended to supports a GridGraph computing messages persistence.
